diary:
It is Friday and that is a half day while COVID-19 is going on at work. So I did not have too much to do.  This week had been hectic with moving and I was exhausted and just spent the day relaxing on the couch watching TV.  Got my normal exercise at home and spent the day watching Bob's Burgers and tried the new show The Great on Hulu.  

One slightly irritating thing with the new apartment is I cannot get the shower head off and that means I cannot use my high power showered, which is making me feel greasy in my hair. But that is a small thing and I will get over it. 

I slept great due to being so exhausted.  So woke up ready for the day.  I think this weekend I will plan to get the old apartment cleaned which will be the final thing I need to do for the apartment and can turn over the keys.

diary:
Woke up feeling refreshed.  The new apartment doesn't have curtains yet so the morning sun is causing me to wake up early (around 7:30) which is a lot earlier than I normally wake up.  

My boyfriends meeting up with some of his friends today in Long Island City which is kind of concerning to me and I feel its not the best thing to do with the current COVID-19 situation.  Not as much because of the virus but drama with others who might hear or see them all together.  He made it home around midnight and was fine which is good. But I don't think the risk was worth it. But I didn't bring it up since I didn't want to cause drama.

I had the first day of class today which was fun and I am excited for this logging and to learn about this process.  I was super excited to hear we are moving the class to Friday instead of Saturday.  So that was a major bonus for the day.

After class I went to the old apartment and cleaned. It took about 6 hours of scrubbing and vacuuming and everything to get everything perfect.  There are still some areas that are just normal wear and a part of the floor that was not sealed and has darkened.  This is causing some stress thinking about the security deposit.  So hopefully all is good here, should know in a bout two weeks after the lease ends.

Otherwise spent the day enjoying the sun (walking between the new and old apartment) and had a basic dinner.  

At the end of the day I noticed two yellow spots on my arm, realized it was bruises from carrying the heavy boxes earlier.  So need to be more careful in the future.  I did the move really cheap (only spent about $100 for the entire move).  So was happy about that but it did take some strain on me with carrying everything.

diary:
Woke up thinking about work and had a plan for creating the class system in the new application I am working on.  After getting up I started writing the system and tests and it ended up taking all day.  Finally around 4pm of nothing but coding I had it stable and ready to push for review.  Unfortunately the people who should review never responded so it is kind of annoying that I worked to get this all ready but the other people are not online to do their part.  

Working all day I never got any food, so need to get a late dinner.  Got a workout on the bike in and showered and got dinner around 8:30. Probably will regret eating so late and will have a little bit of a headache.

The last week I have ordered lots of stuff on Amazon (since I just moved). But it has been irritating that everything is getting delayed. I would be ok with stuff taking longer but they say it will be here on Day X and then every time (if Amazon Logistics shipping) it says this item is delayed and will be here in another 2 days.  Then after 4 days it usually shows up.  It has been making it really hard to plan for the stuff I need to do for the new apartment.

I spent all day working and feel exhausted and my wrists are starting to hurt. Will probably try and take tomorrow easy as long as not too much going on.  

Another small stresses is the payment for the Summer semester at Pratt.  My company shows it it is mailed out nearly a month ago but Pratt doesn't show the payment on my account which makes me nervous. I know a lot of stuff is going on so I emailed the Bursar hopefully they have the check and its not lost, since I don't know what kind of process a lost check is within IBM...

diary_sad_points: Found out that a major massive layoff was happening at work.  This was stressful and saddening thinking about my coworkers and friends who might lose their job. Our group was told we are not part of it and it seems those who are know about it already (based on online forums like Reddit and Facebook). But still stressful thinking about it and saddening thinking about those people trying to get new jobs in this current environment.
diary: The day started off nice.  Took dog on long walk down the Hudson River Park which was nice. Her neck seems better from before but still a little raw so I made sure her harness wasn't near it.  When back at home I went to my old apartment and returned the keys so the old apartment is done now.  Hopefully all is good with the security deposit and no drama.  Around the end of the day I saw an odd meeting from my boss (with lots of people in it) and he posted that he wanted to discuss what is going as we might have heard about layoffs within our company. I had not heard of any, so googled it and quickly found loads of posts.  The meeting indicated we were all safe and would not be laid off. But it is stressful and saddening thinking about the other people who did get laid off and what they are going to do with the current environment. Our boss also mentioned how tough it is for H1B employees who have to find a new job in like 60 days or lose their visa.  This is crazy and I guess in the next few days we will find out more about the people in our larger group who are part of this.  It is very sad and ruined the day.  I hope things get better but with COVID-19 and this I feel terrible for the people.

I think after this we should have everything we need for the new apartment.  Seems weird tomorrow is a holiday. We got some wontons in chili oil, but they were bad too. Seems this place does not do good on dumplings and wontons.  But they through in some chicken feet so Clancy was happy.  It was ok food. We probably won't get it again.
